attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
Jeff is easy to talk to; he was a truck driver for over 20 years. He moved to the Bay Area from Chicago in 1983 because he liked the political and social progressiveness and local music scene.  He has volunteered for numerous environmental causes and political candidates.

Jeff learned to sail at Cal Sailing club (a sailing club affordable to everyone) and he eventually crewed on a small boat to Tahiti and back.

Jeff's commitment to the environment led him to enroll in a public interest law school in San Francisco in order to practice Environmental Law.  He switched to bankruptcy law in 2008 to help people hurt by the economic downturn. Now that the economy has at least temporarily rebounded, Jeff helps people who were wrongfully injured by practicing personal injury law and getting them money damages for their injuries.  He gets great pleasure in helping people, standing up to injustice and sticking it to the banks!
attributes.about_this_biz_history: The Law Office of Jeff D. Hoffman opened in 2003 practicing environmental law.  In 2008, Jeff began practicing bankruptcy law as a way to help the many people suffering from the massive financial hardships created by the bad economy.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties: Jeff handles personal injury, chapter 13 and chapter 7 bankruptcy, loan modifications, and student loan debt. Bankruptcy can stop foreclosures, car repossessions and wage garnishments and can even get rid of some federal or state income taxes.

Just prior to becoming a Realtor, I was a regional sales manager, based in New York, for a mens hosiery line.

I purchased my first piece of real estate when I was 18 years old and have lived in the Oakland neighborhoods of Crocker Highlands, Montclair, Redwood Heights, Glenview, Piedmont Avenue and Hillcrest Highlands,  Berkeley, Stamford (Connecticut) and now reside in Piedmont, California.

Downtown Alameda's Spring Festival (formerly Park Street Spring Festival) has been a favorite for over 15 years. The event is hosted by the Downtown Alameda Business Association and takes place each year during the second weekend of May (Mother's Day weekend).

Located in the East Bay, near Oakland and only 20 minutes from San Francisco, Downtown Alameda's Park Street Business District is the island city's vibrant historic commercial, cultural, and civic center. More than 400 businesses are located in the shopping district and include a variety of restaurants, gift stores, clothing stores, professional services, and amusement centers including the historic Alameda Theatre & Cineplex.

2020 Dates: May 9 & 10 -- 

Downtown Alameda's Spring Festival is a Mother's Day weekend tradition in Alameda and the San Francisco Bay Area. With over 150 vendors, this is a perfect place to find a gift for Mom. Or maybe you would like to treat Mom to a mimosa and lunch at one of the street's food establishments. Located on Park Street between Encinal Avenue and Lincoln Avenue, weekend activities include art & craft vendors, live music, kids' area, food vendors, and beer & wine sales. There is sure to be something for everyone. 

Festival-goers can also stroll along Alameda's vibrant and historic commercial district where shops and restaurants will be offering weekend specials.

A special area for kids and their families on Alameda Avenue features bounce houses, giant slide, slot cars, face painting, and WaterBallerz.

Each day offers continuous live entertainment with popular Bay Area bands performing classic rock, bluegrass, funk, jazz, and soul.

By tailoring each style to the individual’s lifestyle and personality, Pari helps ensure long-lasting results. attributes.about_this_biz_history: Bruce Bauer opened his company in Medford, Oregon in 1938 and after doing some building in the San Mateo county area in 1946, he saw the need for a lumber yard and opened his second store in San Carlos, CA.  Originally opened as a contractor yard, over the years we developed into a do-it-yourself home center with strong emphasis on practical advice to homeowners as a part of our value added service and quality merchandise.  Don Thom bought the lumber yard from his father-in-law, Bruce Bauer in 1966.  In 1971, he bought out Bickell Brothers Lumber at San Antonio Circle in Mountain View.  A family owned business, Don Thom had two of his sons, David and Darryl, working with him.  They had to learn from the bottom up and became familiar with all phases of building including home construction.  We then expanded our inventory to include basic plumbing and electrical supplies, to round out our home improvement materials, service and inventory.  We offer seniors/contractors a discounted rate.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
We are here to help you with decking, windows, or any other home projects!
We sell all types of hardware and stock countless types of lumber.  We also sell tools.  We have a state of the art ANDERSEN window and door show room as well as a MARVIN windows room. VELUX skylights, MILGARD windows are on display as well as TIMBERTECH decking.

Since our family began this business back in 1938, the focus has always been on providing quality customer service. We believe if we consistently achieve a superior level of customer satisfaction in both product quality and service, our entire organization will prosper. We believe by creating a business, which is beneficial to its surrounding communities, that there is a gain as well.

Our long-term success means more than selling a product at a profit. We believe that to succeed over the long term we must excel in:

Treating all customers as our neighbors and friends.
Consistently increasing product knowledge to meet customer needs.
Staff working together as a team to achieve success through service.
Being committed to a professional effort. Being involved in the community.

attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
James Yang is proud to be a full-service Realtor at the Palo Alto office of Sereno Group.

He is an avid mixed martial arts fan, and enjoys spending time reading books on Economics, Psychology, and social interaction.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
Having grown up in the Bay Area, James knows the complexities of the Silicon Valley real estate market like the circuit boards he once built as an electrical engineer.

The UC Berkeley grad followed the path of his parents, both computer scientists who helped Silicon Valley become the high-tech stronghold it is today. But James felt an urge to break out of the box that his upbringing and education had built for him.

He left his engineering job and vaulted into real estate, seeking great mentors along the way. Today, he is one of the top rated agents on the Peninsula as part of the Sereno Group's Palo Alto office.

James practices real estate the way he once competed in Wushu, a contemporary Chinese martial art. He is a tough negotiator who goes to battle for his clients -- while making sure the details are taken care of in the process.

An engineer. A Wushu practitioner. And most recently a CrossFit devotee.  "One of the things I love about engineering, martial arts and CrossFit is that they all share the similar principle of working toward something larger," James says. "Each day, you show up, work on a tiny piece of the project, a small portion of the physical form, or a tiny detail of a barbell lift. Over time, the accumulation of small, daily efforts leads to something great."

From multimillion dollar investment deals to helping a young family find their first home, James thrives on the rigor and unpredictability of a job that has him on call seven days a week.

attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
Harvey Ziff has again been honored as being listed as a 2010 "Northern California Super Lawyer" based on peer recognition and great achievements in representing personal injury plaintiffs.

Ziff attended the Wharton School of Finance, University of Pennsylvania (BS) and Stanford University School of Law. While at Stanford, he served as editor on the Stanford Law Review from 1966-1967. Ziff also earned a masters of law (LLM) from Northwestern University (1969).

After graduating from Stanford University School of Law, Ziff served as a Special Assistant U.S. Attorney in San Francisco from 1968-1969 where he successfully prosecuted felony cases through trial. From 1969-1970 he served as a Deputy Public Defender in Santa Clara County and continued to gain extensive and valuable trial experience.

In 1971, he went into private practice with his partner David Weinberg and shortly after that, decided to dedicate his practice to representing personal injury victims and their families.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
Harvey L. Ziff and Adrienne Z. Cohn offer free initial consultations to all clients involved in personal injury accidents and handle all cases on a contingency fee basis.

You will speak with an experienced Palo Alto personal injury lawyer so that you understand your rights and prospects for a successful resolution of your case.

We are experienced, dedicated, and ready to achieve the best possible results for our clients.

We achieve optimal big firm results at small firm prices.  We practice in all California state and federal courts, private arbitration and administrative hearings.  Pierce & Shearer also provides skilled, cost-effective mediation services.

attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
My father immigrated to the United States after having escaped a communist country. He married my mother who was a citizen but also was from an immigrant family herself. As a result, my father was able to immigrate to the United States through his marriage to my mother, and here I am! I am happy to help people who are in the same place that my family was 45 years ago. This is an area of law that is very rewarding for me.

I am a marriage and family-based immigration lawyer who enjoys his work tremendously. I have helped thousands of immigrants over the past 24 years. 

I finished my Bachelor's Degree in Finance in 1989 at Santa Clara University and my Law Degree in 1992 at McGeorge School of Law (UOP). I was admitted to the California State Bar in 1993 and became a member of AILA (American Immigration Lawyers Association) in the same year. I am also a member of the San Francisco Bar Association's Low-Fee Immigration Panel since 1999.
attributes.about_this_biz_history:
I have been practicing immigration law since I became a lawyer in 1994. My law office handles mostly family-based immigration cases (specializing in marriage to US citizen cases). I belong to the American Immigration Lawyers Association and have been giving advice to the San Francisco Bar Association's Low Fee Referral Program for more than 10 years. I was also named "Lawyer of the Year" and recently nominated as "Best Lawyer in San Francisco."

As a family based immigration lawyer in San Francisco, I bring a level of understanding to my clients that is difficult to duplicate. I believe in the strength of the immigrant heritage of the United States and am passionate about guiding my clients through the complex and sometimes confusing immigration process. I have a detail-oriented and compassionate team, and we will address all of your concerns in a professional, straight forward, easy to understand, and courteous manner.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
I am an attorney specializing in immigration law. For the past 30 years, I have assisted hundreds of individuals and their families obtain legal status in the United States. 

My practice is devoted 100% to U.S. immigration and nationality law. I focus on helping US citizens obtain green cards for their foreign spouses. My rates are very reasonable, payment plans are available, and major credit cards are accepted. My office is conveniently located 1 block from USCIS in San Francisco. I always respond promptly and offer a free telephone consultation.

People who are immigrating to the US must make sure they have all the information they need before proceeding because the process might be complicated and confusing. We provide potential clients with free consultations and examine their specific cases during the discussion. We will answer any questions they may have and provide them with an overview of the immigration process. This way, they will know what to anticipate at each stage. Our goal is to help them navigate the complex immigration process and come up with a plan that's tailored to their specific needs.

attributes.about_this_biz_history: Successfully helping couples resolve the issues around divorce and custody.  Effectively work with employees, employees, unions, businesses, and attorneys to resolve workplace disputes prior to or after litigation has begun.

I successfully mediate cases involving employers and employees, including discrimination cases--disability, pregnancy, race, and sex--wrongful termination, retaliation, wage and hour claims, and help mediate and facilitate requests for reasonable accommodation.  The link between these two areas of my practice is the existence of significant, ongoing relationships, in two of the core parts of life:  work and family.  Clients have complimented my ability to navigate deep emotions and to provide empathy and understanding, while moving the dispute forward to mutual agreement.

attributes.about_this_biz_history: St. Anthony's is a non-profit social services agency located in San Francisco's Tenderloin neighborhood. We were founded by a Franciscan Friar, Fr. Alfred Boeddeker, OFM, in 1950 and are rooted in the Franciscan tradition. In the decades that have passed, much has changed in San Francisco, but St. Anthony's has continued to seek to understand and respond to the social, economic, and political realities that create and sustain poverty and homelessness--realities that directly affect those who come to us for our services and our support.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties: St. Anthony's provides meals, healthcare, clothing, addiction recovery, social services and technology access in the Franciscan spirit to those experiencing homelessness and poverty.

Pet Food Express is here to help California pets and their parents live happier, healthier lives together. We listen, empathize, and collaborate to find answers to the toughest pet problems. Finicky cat? Barking? Leash pulling? We've been there--let us help with our expert advice.Our strategy is simple: we only sell products we trust for our own pets. That means we don't sell products with fillers or suspect ingredients, and we get to know the people we buy products from. Whatever your budget, we'll help you provide the best possible nutrition for your pets.We offer a variety of convenient services. Our self-service pet washes include high-quality shampoos, raised tubs, fresh towels aprons and blow dryers. We partner with VIP Petcare to bring walk-in veterinary services to our stores. We want to be the very best place to shop for your pets. We want you to be able to choose products with confidence, get them how and when you want to, and be sure of our support. Through it all, we want to be a force for good in the greater pet community.

attributes.about_this_biz_bio:
Hello and welcome to Kokio Republic! My name is Nathan, and I am the proud owner of this restaurant. I started this business back in 2014 as a humble food truck serving up the best Korean fried chicken in San Francisco.

As a lover of food and cooking, I spent years perfecting my recipe and techniques, drawing inspiration from my travels throughout Korea and my passion for bold, flavorful dishes. I never imagined that my food truck would grow into the thriving restaurant it is today, but I am so grateful for the support of our loyal customers who have helped make that dream a reality.

At Kokio Republic, we are dedicated to providing our customers with the highest quality food, friendly service, and a warm, inviting atmosphere. Whether you're stopping by for a quick bite, grabbing takeout on the go, or celebrating a special occasion with loved ones, we're here to make your experience unforgettable.

Thank you for choosing Kokio Republic, and I hope to see you soon!
attributes.about_this_biz_history: Our story began in 2014 when we hit the road with our food truck in San Francisco, specializing in Korean fried chicken. Over the years, we gained a loyal following for our unique take on this classic dish, as well as our signature Kimchi Balls and Garlic Cheese Fries. In 2023, we realized our dream of opening a brick-and-mortar location in the city, complete with draft beer and an expanded menu. We're proud to continue offering the same high-quality, flavorful Korean fried chicken that made us a hit on the food truck scene, and we're excited to share our passion for this delicious cuisine with the community.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties: Welcome to Kokio Republic, the home of San Francisco's finest Korean fried chicken. Our journey began in 2014 when we started as a food truck in the city, quickly gaining a loyal following for our mouthwatering KFC, Kimchi Balls, and garlic cheese fries. Today, we offer a wide selection of crispy, flavorful fried chicken, made fresh and served with your choice of sauce. Come dine in, take out, or get delivery and indulge in the best KFC in the Bay Area. With our commitment to quality food and excellent service, we promise you an unforgettable dining experience.
